if -m is the 1st argument and 2nd argument is not dd or rsync, exit 1.
if -v or dd or rsync is the first argument, exit 1.
if -h is the first argument, it should be the only argument. (exit 0). 
if -m is the 2nd argument, exit 1.
if -v is the 2nd argument, exit 1.
if -v is the 3rd argument and $4 doesn't starts with "vol-.{8}", exit 1.


There is a possibility of repetitions. Fix it while putting it down on script.
